On Wednesday, dozens of fighters from an armed group known as Mai-Mai went into the northeastern city of Butembo in the Democratic Republic of Congo and fought with security forces. Their target was an Ebola treatment centre. This comes the region experiences a violent insurgency and armed groups try to turn efforts to fight Ebola into a political tool. Ebola survivors turn caregivers in Congo outbreak Wearing only scrubs and a hair net, Jeanine Masika cradles a two-year-old Ebola patient in her arms. Masika has antibodies in her system after she won her own battle against Ebola last year, and she now has immunity.